Description: AIMS OS — Regular track baseline (slim scientific stack)
 The slim mathematical / scientific computing baseline. Every AIMS
 student gets the SciPy ecosystem (numpy, scipy, pandas, matplotlib,
 seaborn, sympy, scikit-learn, statsmodels, networkx); the classic
 Jupyter Notebook + ipywidgets + the JupyterLab back-end libraries
 (the JupyterLab UI itself is install-on-demand via `pipx install
 jupyterlab` since Debian does not yet package it); R base for the
 statistics modules; gnuplot for plotting; gdb / valgrind for
 debugging; the OpenBLAS / LAPACK / FFTW development headers for
 compiling numerical software; black + mypy for Python code quality;
 and a French-only TeX Live stack (texlive base + latex-extra +
 fonts-extra + lang-french + pictures + biber + latexmk + dvipng)
 sufficient for the typical AIMS Senegal thesis pipeline.
 .
 Heavier / niche scientific tools live in aims-os-math-extras —
 install it to get the full v2.0 stack:
 .
   * Symbolic computing — Maxima + wxMaxima
   * Numerical computing — Octave + scientific modules (symbolic,
     statistics, optim, control, signal)
   * R extras — r-recommended + tidyverse, ggplot2, dplyr, knitr,
     rmarkdown
   * LaTeX extras — English / other-languages (African hyphenation) /
     Arabic / publishers / science / XeTeX / LuaTeX / bibtex-extra,
     TeXstudio
   * Geometry — GeoGebra
   * HPC, bio, image processing — python3-mpi4py, biopython, skimage,
     igraph, rpy2, tables, pygments, reportlab
   * Numerical headers — libhdf5-dev, libgmp-dev, libmpfr-dev
 .
 Coop-track students additionally install aims-os-bigdata (Big Data,
 NLP, Computer Vision, Climate, DB clients) or aims-os-security
 (cryptography, ethical hacking, forensics) on top.
 .
 PyTorch, TensorFlow, JAX, Keras and other rapidly-evolving ML
 frameworks (and Qiskit, PyArrow, Polars, DuckDB, spaCy, gensim,
 HuggingFace Transformers — not yet in Trixie) are deliberately NOT
 included — installation via `mamba install` (Miniforge3 ships in
 aims-os-core's chroot) or `pipx install` is the recommended path
 so students get current versions.
